<body>
	<div class="header">
		<h1>Donate to the BHG Server Fund</h1>
		<h2>(Also known as the Buy Koral A New Bike Fund)</h2>
	</div>
	<div class="donate">
		<h2>Paypal</h2>
		<div class="center">
			<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post">
				<p>
					<input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_s-xclick">
					<input type="image" src="https://www.paypal.com/en_US/i/btn/x-click-but21.gif" border="0" name="submit" alt="Make payments with PayPal - it's fast, free and secure!">
					<img alt="" border="0" src="https://www.paypal.com/en_AU/i/scr/pixel.gif" width="1" height="1">
					<input type="hidden" name="encrypted" value="-----BEGIN PKCS7----------END PKCS7-----
		">
				</p>
			</form>
		</div>
		<p>Those with paypal accounts. I can not accept direct CCs through Paypal. They want
		money per month for that.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="donate">
		<h2>Paymate</h2>
		<div class="center">
			<p>
				<a onclick="self.name = 'parent';" target="_blank" href="https://www.paymate.com.au/PayMate/ExpressPayment?mid=adamashley"><img src="https://www.paymate.com.au/images/DonateNow_btn.gif" border="0" alt="Pay with Paymate Express"></a>
			</p>
		</div>
		<p>Use this if you just want to donate with a CC without setting up a Paypal account.</p>
	</div>
	<p>Keeping the server up and running is an expensive and time consuming proposition. Until
	2004 I had been funding it all myself, at the time it was costing me US$109, approximately
	10% of my after tax take home pay. I could not keep this up, so started looking for donations.
	Now the server is cheaper US$69 a month and considerably more powerful.</p>
	<p>So feel free to donate as little or as much as you want. And remember donate and you
	get the contributors access to the <a href="http://www.lyarna.net/">free hosting</a>.</p>
